tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control (diabetes or prediabetes). Cholesterol and triglycerides are also elevated, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk. Renal function, electrolytes, and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend review of diabetes and lipid management.
